The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Friday, February 04, 2005 

 Musharraf memoir in the works

 Musharraf

 New York, Feb. 3 (Reuters): Pakistani President Pervez Musharraf has sold the rights to his political memoir, which will feature his views on the US war on terrorism and the Bush administration, to Simon amp; Schuster imprint Free Press, the publisher said yesterday.

 Musharraf, a key Bush administration ally as it has pursued wars in Afghanistan and Iraq after the September 11, 2001, attacks, showed his proposal to several New York publishers before accepting a bid for world rights from Free Press. 

 The book will be published in autumn next year 2006, Free Press vice-president and senior editor Bruce Nichols said. ?He?s going to cover the war on terror from Afghanistan in the 1970s and 1980s up to the hunt for Osama bin Laden,? Nichols said. 




